This informs the user which target addresses the notification was sent to.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fI{snmp_notification, tag(), {got_response, Address}}\fR

.PP
This informs the user that this target address acknowledged the notification.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fI{snmp_notification, tag(), {no_response, Address}}\fR

.PP
This informs the user that this target address did not acknowledge the notification.

.RE

.PP
The notification is sent as an Inform-Request to each target address in \fIAddresses\fR and if there are no targets for which an Inform-Request is sent, \fIAddresses\fR is the empty list \fI[]\fR.

.PP
The \fItag_receiver()\fR will first be sent the \fIsnmp_targets\fR message, and then for each address in \fIAddresses\fR list, one of the two \fIsnmp_notification\fR messages.


.RE

{Mod, Func, Args}
.RS 2
The info will be delivered via the function call:

.PP
\fIMod:Func([Msg | Args])\fR

.PP
where \fIMsg\fR has the same content and purpose as the messages descrived above.


.RE


.RE

.PP
The 'process oid' "tag" that can be provided with the variable name / oids is intended to be used for oid post processing. The value '\fIkeep\fR', which is the default, leaves the oid as is. The value '\fItruncate\fR', will cause the oid to be "truncated". That is, any trailing ".0" will be removed.

.PP
\fBNOTE: \fRThere is a way to exclude a varbind from the notification. In the normal \fIvarbinds\fR list, providing the special value \fI'$ignore-oid'\fR (instead of a normal value) will exclude this varbind from the notification. A define for this has been added to the \fIsnmp_types.hrl\fR include file, \fINOTIFICATION_IGNORE_VB_VALUE\fR.


.PP
\fBNOTE: \fRThe \fIextra\fR info is not normally interpreted by the agent, instead it is passed through to the net-if process. It is up to the implementor of that process to make use of this data. The version of net-if provided by this application makes no use of this data, with one exception: Any tuple containing the atom \fIsnmpa_default_notification_extra_info\fR may be used by the agent and is therefore \fIreserved\fR. See the net-if incoming messages for sending a trap and notification for more info.



